title: For Sale:  FLIR T70 Thermal clip on sight
postcontent:
Selling my FLIR T70 Advanced Combat Thermal Sight- Short Range in FDE.  I have had this unit since I bought it new in November of 2013 from TNVC.  I have used it a total of three times, and it has sat in my safe with the batteries out for the rest of its boring life.  Selling it because I just don't use it.  It is in as new condition; looks and functions flawlessly and includes all original accessories, as well as an adapter I bought at RadioShack that allows you to plug the external video cable into a TV.  If you are considering this unit then you probably already know all about it.  It can function as both a clip on in front of your day scope, or as a stand alone weapon sight with its built in reticle. It has a native 640x512 sensor with an advanced OLED display.  This unit is rated to handle recoil up to and including .50BMG.  It has the traditional grayscale color pallets with white hot/black hot, but also offers several other options like a full color aka rainbow pallete, iron pallete, and a fire and ice pallete where you see a traditional grayscale pallete but with the added bonus of hot objects appearing red and cold objects appearing blue. It also features FLIR's DDE mode as an option.  DDE is basically a spatial filter designed to enhance the high spatial frequencies (edges etc.) of objects, giving the image a more "real", textured look.  This unit has a 0.5x or wide field of view mode which offers an excellent FOV, and was perfect for me when used in conjunction with a 4x ACOG as it provided a 2x total magnification (.5x X 4x) which was excellent for fast, close in shooting.  It also has a 1x mode and a 2x mode, which would offer 4x and 8x total magnifications when used in conjunction with a 4x ACOG.  This can all be adjusted via the controls on the side of the unit, as well as with a remote control that comes with it that allows you to place the exact controls wherever you want on your rifle.  If you are looking for the ultimate thermal clip-on sight for short range (up to 6x) optics, look no further.

 Retail price on these is $14,900.

I will ship to the continental U.S. with payment via bank wire transfer only
A FTF sale in southwest Florida is also an option, I will be able to meet and show the item to serious buyers on or after the 30th of June as I am currently out of town, eastern PA.

title: For Sale/Trade:  COLT 1911 Rail Gun / Bi-tone Stainless and Black Model. Absolutely pristine!
postcontent:
Not much needs to be said about this 1911. If you are looking at this you already know what it is. It's a thing of beauty is what it is! So much so that I'm scared to put it into a holster and scuff up the finish! This thing is absolutely pristine!

This gun has no handling scratches. No idiot marks. Notice the trigger and beaver tail grip safety have almost NO noticeable finish wear? The stainless slide has no scratches on the finish either. In fact if I didn't tell you I had shot this gun, I could pass this off and brand new.

This pistol has one box 50 round box threw it and it's been played with using plastic/brass snap-caps, that's it!

This thing spent most of it's life oiled down, in it's original plastic bag and case. I was going to put some different grips on it, add some night sights etc but I just never did. I was so paranoid about messing it up I just wanted to leave it as is.

As this is a standard barrel and bushing setup, this would be perfect for IDPA for those of you who want to use a 1911. The extra meat on the end of the frame (the rail) helps balance the pistol out but it's not heavy at all.

This is the stainless model with the Black Cerakoted frame and semi-black grips as you can see from the photo.

As most of you know COLT just filed bankruptcy. They also just discontined their XSE and Rail Gun lines of pistols so these are about to start getting hard to find. I like the way this looks but I'm too scared to do anything with it for fear or ruining the value.

A quick check of Gunbroker tells me they are going for around $1100~1150.00 and most people are charging another 25~50.00 for shipping plus don't forget your FFL fee's. Haven't seen one of these locally in a long while now.

I'm after a trade. I'm looking for something from Heckler and Koch. More specifically something in .45ACP. I do not want their older USP's though. I want something like the HK45CT or HK45T. Not too concerned with the condition as I intend to shoot the piss out of it anyway but I would really prefer something with a threaded barrel as I have a Ti-Rant 45S but I'm open to offers.

I MAY also consider one of the HK P30L's in 9mm but I'm after a .45ACP first as I already have a GLOCK 17, 19, M&P 9 full-size, M&P9 Shield etc. The only .45ACP's I have are a couple COLT 1911's and I'd really like a HK so I've got something for the upcoming Zombie Apocalypse!

Shoot me an email if you want to talk more. I would also take cash to buy what I want. I put $1000.00 dollars but I'm open to REASONABLE offers. If I have to ship, that's on your dime.

I'm located in the Rockford / Grand Rapids area and would like to keep this as semi-local as possible as I drive an old SUV with crap gas mileage.
